---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const lastUpdated = 'June 15, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Minimatod handles your data. Short version: your notes and tasks stay on your device."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-20 sm:py-28">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 leading-relaxed text-muted">
      <p class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-ink-soft p-5 text-paper">
        <strong>In short:</strong> {SITE.name} stores your notes and tasks
        locally on your device. We do not collect, sell, or share your personal
        data, and you don’t need an account to use the app.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-paper">Information we collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {SITE.name} does not require an account and does not collect personal
          information. The notes and tasks you create are stored only on your
          device (and, for the web app, locally in your browser). We have no
          access to that content.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-paper">How your data is stored</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Your content is saved in a local database on your device. It stays
          there until you delete it or remove the app. Uninstalling the app
          deletes its local data.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-paper">Third-party services</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The app itself does not send your content to third parties. If you
          download {SITE.name} from the Apple App Store or Google Play, those
          platforms may collect their own analytics (for example, downloads and
          crashes) under their respective privacy policies.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-paper">Future features</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We plan to add optional cloud sync and paid features in the future. If
          you choose to enable them, some data (such as your notes and account
          details) would be transmitted and stored to make those features work.
          This policy will be updated before any such feature is released, and
          those features will be opt-in.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-paper">Children’s privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {SITE.name} is not directed to children under 13 and does not knowingly
          collect personal information from them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-paper">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on
          this page with a new “last updated” date.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-paper">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions about this policy? Email
          <a
            href={`mailto:${SITE.privacyEmail}`}
            class="text-paper underline underline-offset-4">{SITE.privacyEmail}</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
